<br>
However, I'm still going to assume that when I meet a guy carrying a flaming sword, he's a worshipper of the light gods, and therefore my enemy.  That's how Didi knows the world.  Her player knows that maybe the paladin may be a bastard (considering some of the paladins who post on the soapbox, highly likely actually).  But Didi knows nothing of the paladin's background, actions, character, or story and is going to treat a paladin like a paladin.  Didi takes SOE's description of the races and classes as her base assumption, what she was taught as she grew up, unless proved differently.  Unless circumstances happen to show her that paladin is different (e.g. he's KOS in all the good cities, consistently worships the dark gods, and kills light-worshippers) she will have no reason to change her mind.<br>
<br>
And may I say there are too many paladins claiming to be evil who really just help out whichever side, good or evil, that they feel like at the moment.  That's not evil, that's self-serving chaotic.  Likewise all the dark elves claiming to be good.  I have met ONE, only ONE, who supported that with the faction work to enter Kelethin and the 'good' cities.  Simply running around saying &quot;I'm good&quot; while still amiable in Neriak and KOS in Felwithe does not make player of Didi consider you to be 'good', just more self-serving chaotic.<br>
<br>
You say you ally with the Sarnaks?  OK, better not be KOS in Chardok.  You say you ally with the Coldain?  OK, better not be KOS in Thurgadin.  You say you ally with the 'good' races?  OK, come meet me in Kaladim, or Kelethin, or Felwithe.  I say I'm allied with the gnomes, and I'll meet you in Ak'Anon any time.  I'd be ashamed to claim any such thing if I hadn't done the faction work.  In short - kudos to those who wish to roleplay something a little different, but (a) character of Didi (being a racist dark elf) will still judge them on their race and class until she sees something different, and (b) player of Didi isn't going to have a lot of respect for that claim if they haven't backed it up with the real faction work. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caillougna>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/dot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pebble with a bow</span><br>  Posts: 1819<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/11/03 11:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3826.topic&index=68>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/sigs/smile.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hm</span><hr size=1> [quote}Basically, these peoples' guild charter wrecked my fun.[/quote]<br>
<br>
Without quoting the rest of it... this one line can be used to evoke it.  You blather on and on how it is interferring with YOU as if you, your fun, and your XP bar are the only things which are important.  The guild's charter might be heightening the fun of those who refused to group with you based on the fact you are of a proscribed race or class.  But that isn't possible in your world because it interfers with YOUR fun.  <br>
<br>
If you really want to RP with someone, there are a thousand ways to do so without grouping with them to kill things.  No, it likely would not move your XP bar an iota, but, to some of us, that is not the only definition of &quot;fun&quot;.  In fact, the conversation in /say might well have been exactly the sort of experience they were looking for at that time and your contributing to that would not move your XP bar but could give you an experience as well.<br>
<br>
Again..... it seems the opponents to RP have the ONLY arguement that it interfers with their single player game.  News flash, EQ is not single player and their is no requirement for RPers to enchance your fun at the expense of their own.  Most RPers won't stop you from not RPing (as long as you don't give them grief for RPing), so why is their RPing without you such a threat to you? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=isharramoonsong>Isharra Moonsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Custom Title Repo'd</span><br>  Posts: 1162<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/12/03 6:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3826.topic&index=69>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~brennec/_uimages/Isharra.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Labeling &quot;Evil&quot; and &quot;Good&quot;</span><hr size=1> /sigh <br>
